UML:Class.name: List of Elements in Package ISO 19103:2015 Conceptual schema language

UML:TaggedValue.value: Specifies information items for describing a cross-map register and its subregisters.
Specifies elements of information to be recorded for each terminological entry in a reference vocabulary.
Connects an instance of CrossMapRegisterItem to an instance of ReferenceVocabularyEntry.
<<enumeration>> that provides values for describing the relationship of an operating concept to a reference concept.
The reference concept and operating concept are identical.
The reference concept is a generalization of the operating concept.
The reference concept is a specialization of the operating concept.
The reference concept and operating concept share characteristics inherited from a common superordinate concept.
The reference concept is a component of the operating concept.
The reference concept is an aggregation of two or more operating concepts.
The relationship between the reference concept and the operating concept is specified by a user-defined classification system.
There is no relationship between the operating concept and the reference concept.
Used in the principal register to describe affiliated subregisters.
General statement of the purpose for which items in the subregister are made available to potential users.
Specifies whether a subregister is a reference vocabulary (0 = No, 1 = Yes).
Summary of alternative locales used by items in a subregister, represented as instances of the class RE_Locale.
<<enumeration>> that provides values for describing the relationship of an operating term to a reference term.
The reference term is identical to the operating term and designates the same concept
The reference term and operating term are different but designate the same concept
The reference term and operating term are identical but designate distinctly different concepts that share certain characteristics.
The reference term and operating term are identical but designate distinctly different concepts that share no characteristics.
There is no relationship between the reference term and operating term.
Specifies elements of management information to be recorded for each proposal to clarify a cross-map entry.
Specifies elements of information to be recorded for each terminological entry in an operating vocabulary.
Connects an instance of CrossMapRegisterItem to an instance of OperatingVocabularyEntry.
Specifies elements of information to be recorded for each cross-map entry in a cross-map subregister.
Relationship of the reference term to the operating term represented as an instance of the enumeration TermRelationship
Information supporting the determination of termRelationship
Relationship of the reference concept to the operating concept, represented as an instance of the enumeration ConceptRelationship
Information supporting the determination of conceptRelationship

Reference to a resource describing the user-defined classification system adopted to describe concept relationships. Note to entry: This attribute is conditional. It shall only be used if a user-defined classification system for concept relationships has been adopted.
Specifies elements of management information to be recorded for each proposal to add a cross-map entry.
Specifies elements of management information to be recorded for each proposal to amend a cross-map entry.
